1's complement:

  eg. given no is 13.
  
  the number as represented in binary format is 
  
  (13) -> (1101)
  
  flipping the bits, the number will be
  
  (0010)
  
  This is the 1's complement of the number given, 13.


2's complement:

  1. Figure out the 1's complement of a number
  2. Add 1 to the 1's complement

  for 13, 1's complemnt is (0010)
  and adding 1 to it gives, (0011), which is 2's complement of 13.

  
